            I am studying a PhD in Statistics at The University of
            Auckland. My aim is to develop statistical models for
            dimensionality reduction and apply Bayesian networks to
            determine the interconnections of components within a
            complex ecological ecosystem.
            I am interested and curious about all things DATA. This
            includes anything from designing surveys, collecting,
            mining, cleansing, analysing and visualisation to obtain
            data-driven insights from the data. I enjoy data wrangling
            data, building tools and automating processes. This means I
            do data analytics/machine learning consultation (besides my
            PhD) and enjoy working in collaborative and socially diverse
            environments.
